Frequently Asked Questions for Paramount Gold Nevada Corp (ARCA:PZG)
What is Paramount Gold Nevada Corp's stock symbol?

Paramount Gold Nevada Corp trades on the ARCA under the ticker symbol "PZG."



Where is Paramount Gold Nevada Corp's stock going? Where will Paramount Gold Nevada Corp's stock price be in 2017?

1 analysts have issued 1-year target prices for Paramount Gold Nevada Corp's shares. Their predictions range from $2.30 to $2.30. On average, they anticipate Paramount Gold Nevada Corp's share price to reach $2.30 in the next year. View Analyst Ratings for Paramount Gold Nevada Corp.



Who are some of Paramount Gold Nevada Corp's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Paramount Gold Nevada Corp include Golden Minerals Co (AUMN), General Moly (GMO), Bushveld Minerals Limited (BMN), Banro (BAA), Jubilee Platinum PLC (JLP), Plant Health Care plc (PHC), Trans-Siberian Gold plc (TSG), Beowulf Mining plc (BEM), Marrone Bio Innovations (MBII), Applied Graphene Materials PLC (AGM), Clean Diesel Technologies (CDTI), Amur Minerals (AMC), Uranium Resources (URRE), Comstock Mining (LODE), Wolf Minerals Limited (WLFE), Thompson Creek Metals Company (TC), Magnum Hunter Resources Corp (MHR) and Serabi Gold PLC (SRB).



Who are Paramount Gold Nevada Corp's key executives?

Paramount Gold Nevada Corp's management team includes the folowing people: Glen Van Treek, President, Chief Executive Officer, DirectorRudi P. Fronk, Independent Non-Executive Chairman of the BoardDavid Stewart Smith, Non-Executive DirectorJohn R. Carden Ph.D., Independent DirectorEliseo Gonzalez-Urien, Independent DirectorPierre Pelletier, Independent Director



How do I buy Paramount Gold Nevada Corp stock? 

Shares of Paramount Gold Nevada Corp can be purchased through any online brokerage account. Popular online brokerages include Vanguard Brokerage Services, TD Ameritrade, E*TRADE, Scottrade, Fidelity and Charles Schwab. 


